                </p> </i> </b>

                <br> <br>

                <h3 style="text-align: center;">1|<br>
                    Calangute Beach</h3>

                <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.curiouskeeda.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/goa-beach-curiouskeeda.png?resize=640%2C387&ssl=1"
                    width="100%" height="auto"><br><br>

                <p>
                    Known as the Queen of Beaches, the Calangute beach has all qualities to give guests an
                    all-encompassing beach experience. Being the biggest one in North Goa, the activities here are
                    seeing art exhibits at the Kerkar Art Complex and visiting the open market to buy high-quality
                    handmade products. The beach likewise is also known for some invigorating water sports in Goa like
                    surfing, parasailing, and water skiing. The best way to explore Calangute, you can hire a bicycle
                    and roam around as well.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Some famous bars and eateries are Oriental, and Tibetan Kitchen. Renzo’s Inn Beach Resort is a
                    notable hotel here. There are not one but rather multiple beach shacks. Prince of Tides is viewed as
                    the best among them. Goa springs up during Christmas; Calangute is even more unique. The best season
                    to visit is late October – which is regular for most beaches in North Goa.
                </p>


                <h3 style="text-align: center;">2|<br>
                    Baga Beach</h3>

                <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.curiouskeeda.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/goa-baga-beach-curiouskeeda-jetsave.jpg?resize=640%2C427&ssl=1"
                    width="100%" height="auto"><br><br>

                <p>
                    If you are searching for a beach where you can unwind and luxuriate some sun, tuning in to the
                    waves, Baga Beach is probably the best beaches in Goa for loved day out. It is said that party never
                    stops on Baga beach. If the uproarious bars are not for you, an evening time walk around Baga can
                    get entirely great. A portion of the retreats by this beach is Pride resort, Angelina beach resort,
                    and Blue Marine Beach Resort. Baga beach is celebrated for an assortment of water sports in Goa,
                    people come here to appreciate a lot of water sports. Speed drifting is a positive must attempt, so
                    is the Bumpy Ride, where you sit on a cylinder attached to a vessel, which is hauled over the water
                    by a speed pontoon. What better right?
                </p>

                <h3 style="text-align: center;">3|<br>
                    Candolim Beach</h3>

                <img src="https://i0.wp.com/www.curiouskeeda.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/goa-candolim-beach.jpg?resize=640%2C480&ssl=1"
                    width="100%" height="auto"><br><br>

                <p>
                    This is a well-known beach that is also situated in North Goa and it’s ideal for those looking for
                    rushes and enjoyment in the sun. It’s one of the three celebrated trio of most mainstream sea shores
                    in Goa: Baga, Calangute, and Candolim. And it’s no surprise why. It’s a bustling beach with sun beds
                    lined over, so it’s an extraordinary spot to get a tan. There are likewise a great deal of water
                    sports openings on this sea shore including, banana pontoon rides, parasailing and fly ski rides.
                </p>

                <h3 style="text-align: center;">4|<br>
                    Sinquerim Beach</h3>

                <img src="https://i0.wp.com/www.curiouskeeda.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/goa-sinquerim-beach.jpg?resize=640%2C427&ssl=1"
                    width="100%" height="auto"><br><br>

                <p>
                    Sinquerim Beach is a delightful beach with a huge region of brilliantly golden sand. You can
                    likewise explore the Aguada Fort that adds a picturesque setting to the site. It is among the best
                    seashores in Goa to try water rides and other water experiences. At the point when you feel hungry
                    after the energizing and depleting water-experiences, head directly to the nourishment slows down to
                    evaluate some quick Goan-munchies.
                </p>

                <h3 style="text-align: center;">5|<br>
                    Morjim Beach</h3>

                <img src="https://i0.wp.com/www.curiouskeeda.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/goa-morjim-beach.jpg?w=550&ssl=1"
                    width="100%" height="auto"><br><br>

                <p>
                    Alluded to as the Turtle Beach, Morjim Beach is settled in the midst of verdant regions. Tranquil
                    and segregated, this sea shore is for people who are in search for harmony and calm with their
                    friends and family. It is perhaps the best beach in Goa for some quiet climate. Morjim Beach is one
                    of the unexplored beach in Goa that you should visit. Later at night, you could go to one of the
                    casinos in Goa to attempt your luck. <b>(What if you hit a jackpot?) </b>
                </p>

